SUMMARY:Lancaster Breakfast and History Walking Tour
DESCRIPTION:Searching for a walking history tour in Lancaster? You’re in for a flavorful experience—literally! \n\n\nIntroducing the Lancaster History & Breakfast Walking Tour—a dynamic two-hour adventure that blends the rich heritage of one of America’s oldest inland cities with a delicious morning meal. Explore Lancaster’s vibrant streets with a professionally trained local guide and journey through time from the early 1700s through the transformative decades of the 20th century. \n\n\nBrought to you by Unique Lancaster Experiences\, this guided walk kicks off with your choice of hot or iced coffee or tea to energize your morning. Along the way\, you’ll hear engaging stories about Lancaster’s evolution as a bustling Market City and its transition from trolleys to automobiles after WWI. \n\n\nBut this isn’t your standard history tour. You’ll dive into interactive discussions and uncover captivating insights about colonial life\, architectural landmarks\, and the impact of prohibition on the region. \n\n\nAs you explore\, you’ll stop at five handpicked local spots to enjoy a curated tasting menu featuring hearty breakfast sandwiches\, fresh fruits\, sweet pastries\, and other morning favorites. \n\n\nPlease note: This tour offers vegetarian-friendly options only. If you have other dietary needs\, we recommend our International Food Tour for a better fit. \n\n\nWhether you’re passionate about history\, love discovering new flavors\, or just want a memorable way to see the city\, the Lancaster History & Breakfast Tour is a great choice for solo explorers\, couples\, and groups alike.
URL:https://lancasterpa.com/events-calendar/lancaster-breakfast-and-history-walking-tour/2026-04-10/
LOCATION:Unique Lancaster\, 23 N Walnut Street\, Lancaster\, 17603\, United States
CATEGORIES:Children & Family events,Food & Beverage Events,Lancaster City,Tour
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://lancasterpa.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/unique-lancaster-experiences-event-breakfast-tour.png
END:VEVENT
